OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1774991532
OL,3,CMortgage rates set to keep rising,
OL,4,Cwarns former NatWest chair
OL,6,FDavies points out that before the
OL,7,Ffinancial crisis of 2007 to 2008, most
OL,8,Fpeople had variable-rate mortgages
OL,9,Fwhich rose and fell in line with
OL,10,Finterest rates.
OL,12,FSince then, the UK has moved to a
OL,13,Fsystem where borrowers fix their
OL,14,Fmortgages for set periods - and can
OL,15,Fface sudden "cliff edges" when those
OL,16,Fdeals end.
OL,18,FBorrowing costs in the UK have risen
OL,19,Ffaster than in the US and the Eurozone
OL,20,Fbecause investors see Britain as more
OL,21,Fexposed to inflation.
OL,26,@wD@MOUwD@YO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
