CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1774991532
OL,3,CMortgage rates set to keep rising,
OL,4,Cwarns former NatWest chair
OL,6,FMarkets are currently pricing in two
OL,7,Finterest rate rises before the end of
OL,8,Fthe year.
OL,10,FBut Davies argues that while higher
OL,11,Fenergy prices will push inflation up,
OL,12,Fthey will also hit demand.
OL,14,FHis view is that the market reaction
OL,15,Fto the war is probably "exaggerated" -
OL,16,Fand that the Bank of England is likely
OL,17,Fto wait and see how the situation
OL,18,Fdevelops.
OL,26,@wD@XOUwD@dO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,303,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30206
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1774991532
OL,3,CMortgage rates set to keep rising,
OL,4,Cwarns former NatWest chair
OL,6,FThe government says it is prepared to
OL,7,Foffer support to households and
OL,8,Fbusinesses to cushion the impact of
OL,9,Fthe energy shock.
OL,11,FDavies says targeted help - such as
OL,12,Fhardship funds for those on benefits
OL,13,Fand the most vulnerable - would be
OL,14,F"perfectly reasonable".
OL,16,FBut he warns that broader, universal
OL,17,Fsupport risks fuelling inflation and
OL,18,F"isn't going to cause more tankers to
OL,19,Fcome through the Strait of Hormuz".
OL,26,@vD@AOUvD@VO]zD@AOU{D@bO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,303,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30207
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1774991532
OL,3,CMortgage rates set to keep rising,
OL,4,Cwarns former NatWest chair
OL,6,F"I think reasonable people will say
OL,7,Fthe government didn't cause this
OL,8,Fproblem," he added. "And it's not
OL,9,Fpolitically catastrophic for it to
OL,10,Fallow this to play out."
OL,12,FWith pressure mounting on ministers to
OL,13,Fact, Davies believes a squeeze on
OL,14,Fliving standards is inevitable - and
OL,15,Fthat households should be prepared to
OL,16,Ftighten their belts and ride the shock
OL,17,Fout in the months ahead.
OL,26,@pD@IO]pD@UOUrD@XO]
